# Task 4: Password Cracking Lab

## Overview
This folder documents the password cracking exercises performed using access
gained in Task 3. The /etc/shadow file was extracted from Metasploitable 2,
password hashes were saved to Kali Linux, and John the Ripper was used to
crack them. Cracked credentials were then validated via SSH login.

---

## Environment
| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Attacker | Kali Linux |
| Target | Metasploitable 2 — 192.168.56.101 |
| Tool | John the Ripper 1.9.0-Jumbo-1 |
| Hash Type | md5crypt ($1$) |
| Date | 8 May 2026 |

---

## Prerequisites
- Root shell access on Metasploitable 2 (obtained in Task 3)
- John the Ripper installed on Kali

```bash
sudo apt install john
```

---

## Lab Walkthrough

### Step 1 — Extract hashes from /etc/shadow
Inside the Metasploit root shell:
```bash
cat /etc/shadow
```
Copy the lines with real hash values (those containing `$1$`).
Accounts with `*` or `!` have no password set and can be ignored.

